# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok new research on the conflict in sudan 's western darfur region shows that more than ## percent of the ###,### deaths since fighting began in #### were the result of disease , not violence .
# ::alignments
(s / show-01
      :ARG0 (r / research-01
            :ARG1 (c / conflict-01
                  :location (c2 / country-region
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Western"
                              :op2 "Darfur")
                        :location (c3 / city
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Sudan"))))
            :ARG1-of (n3 / new-01))
      :ARG1 (r2 / result-01
            :polarity -
            :ARG1 (d / disease)
            :ARG2 (d2 / die-01
                  :ARG1-of (ii / include-91
                        :ARG2 (d3 / die-01
                              :ARG1-of (c4 / cause-01
                                    :ARG0 (f / fight-01
                                          :ARG1-of (b / begin-01
                                                :location (w / world-region
                                                      :name (n4 / name
                                                            :op1 "West"
                                                            :op2 "Darfur"))))))
                        :ARG3 (m / more-than
                              :op1 (p / percent))))
            :ARG1-of (c5 / contrast-01
                  :ARG2 (r3 / result-01
                        :polarity -
                        :ARG1 (v / violence)
                        :ARG2 d2))))

                  :location (ii / inside
                        :op1 (t2 / tunnel)))

                  :quant (a2 / at-least
                        :op1 3))
            :time (w / wednesday)
            :time (a3 / after
                  :op1 (k2 / kill-01
                        :ARG0 (c3 / crash-01
                              :ARG1-of (r2 / resemble-01))
                        :ARG1 (p3 / person
                              :quant 5
                              :ARG0-of t)
                        :mod (c4 / country
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Netherlands")))
                  :quant (m / multiple
                        :op1 (t3 / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 1
                              :unit (d / day))
                        :mod (j / just)))))
